## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart.

### Changes Made

**1. Installed Package:**
- Added `@vercel/analytics` version ^2.0.1 to dependencies
- Used npm to install the package (matching the project's existing package manager)
- Updated package-lock.json with the new dependency tree

**2. Modified Files:**
- **portal/package.json**: Added `@vercel/analytics` to dependencies
- **portal/package-lock.json**: Updated with new package and its dependencies
- **portal/src/app/layout.tsx**: 
  - Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
  - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the body element (after children)

### Implementation Details

The Analytics component was added to the root layout file (`src/app/layout.tsx`) following Next.js App Router best practices:
- Imported from `@vercel/analytics/next` (framework-specific export)
- Placed at the end of the body element to avoid blocking page rendering
- Preserves all existing code structure and styling

### Verification Steps Completed

✅ **Linting**: Ran `npm run lint` - No ESLint warnings or errors
✅ **Build**: Ran `npm run build` - Compiled successfully with no errors
✅ **Tests**: Ran `npm test` - All 28 test suites passed (151 tests total)
✅ **Lock Files**: package-lock.json updated correctly

### Next Steps

To enable analytics tracking in production:
1. Deploy this application to Vercel
2. Navigate to the project dashboard on Vercel
3. Go to the Analytics section and click "Enable" button
4. After the next deployment, analytics will be active at `/_vercel/insights/*` routes

The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation exactly and is ready for production use.
